        "toc_item_2": {
          "type": "toc_item",
          "settings": {
            "anchor_id": "from-tooth-to-toe",
            "title": "From tooth to toe — total alignment",
            "subitems": "<ul><li>Support from the foundation to the crown</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "toc_item_3": {
          "type": "toc_item",
          "settings": {
            "anchor_id": "the-biomechaneer-story",
            "title": "The Biomechaneer story: why these are different",
            "subitems": "<ul><li>Why generic spacers weren't enough</li><li>Systemic improvements</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "point_1": {
          "type": "point",
          "settings": {
            "anchor_id": "supporting-your-bodys-foundation",
            "layout": "image_left",
            "eyebrow": "Foundation",
            "title": "Supporting your body's",
            "title_accent": "foundation",
            "subtitle": "",
            "body": "<p>The ergonomic design of these toe spacers restores the natural width of the forefoot—a structural necessity commonly lost to modern footwear.</p><p>By encouraging a wider base, the device recovers your natural alignment from the ground up.</p>",
            "bullets": "",
            "callout_title": "Usage tip.",
            "callout": "<p>Wear the separators progressively — start with a few minutes and build up to a few hours each day to maximize the benefits.</p>",
            "footer_line": "From tooth to toe: this is the support your body needs.",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/a2483dbc8abf3b391ef806fd152bd0af0dbb4ff5_d8635609-42b8-4a18-a148-1068ea802610.png"
          }
        },
        "point_2": {
          "type": "point",
          "settings": {
            "anchor_id": "from-tooth-to-toe",
            "layout": "image_right",
            "eyebrow": "Total Alignment",
            "title": "From tooth",
            "title_accent": "to toe",
            "subtitle": "Support From the Foundation to the Crown",
            "body": "<p>To truly optimize the human body, you must address its two most critical sensory and structural anchors: <strong>the feet and the teeth</strong>.</p><p>The feet provide your physical base. The teeth act as the fundamental support for your skull.</p><p>When both are supported, you remove the primary tension points that lead to chronic pain and structural collapse.</p><p>We believe that by combining the Reviv mouthguard with these toe separators, you achieve <strong>two-directional biomechanical restoration:</strong></p>",
            "bullets": "<ul><li>Untwist your skeleton, expand your skull</li><li>Improve structural-related body functions</li><li>Become stronger, more flexible, more symmetrical</li></ul>",
            "callout_title": "",
            "callout": "",
            "footer_line": "",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/8d8d229321e2bf5a94d1aa5106d067b10205dc6c_6a1040d6-47ab-4029-947f-7ee41f85e5bf.jpg"
          }
        },
        "point_story_Aigafg": {
          "type": "point_story",
          "settings": {
            "anchor_id": "",
            "title": "The Biomechaneer story: <br>why these are",
            "title_accent": "different",
            "subtitle": "Support From the Foundation to the Crown",
            "image_1": "shopify://shop_images/a3846c466c370abf62b16b3ad7a19d7399c03b91.jpg",
            "text_1": "<p>As I've seen from my physiotherapy training, feet play a huge role in postural balance and alignment. However, most people ignore how much toe splay determines overall function. <br/><br/>Sadly, modern-day footwear is unintentionally designed to sabotage this. The narrow toe box found in most footwear gradually cramps the toes together, compromising the very base we stand on. <br/><br/><strong>When the base fails, the entire structure of the body suffers.</strong></p>",
            "image_2": "shopify://shop_images/91b369920e5bcf4152ba94551e329c25ff321862.jpg",
            "heading_2": "Why generic spacers weren't enough",
            "text_2": "<p>Toe separators aim to reverse this process. However, most brands fall short in their attempt. <br/><br/>I've personally been part of the \"barefoot\" community for years, wearing generic spacers and switching exclusively to barefoot shoes. While I noticed increased mobility and strength, I only restored part of the damage. <br/><br/>With my teeth still locked in an occlusion, my skull remained restricted, making further progress difficult. <strong>After freeing up both tension points, progress accelerated.</strong></p>",
            "bottom_intro": "<p>Once combined with a Reviv mouthguard, any positive postural intervention simply sticks much more easily. As a result, this gave me: </p>",
            "bottom_bullets": "<ul><li><strong>Improved balance</strong> — a wider forefoot area creates a more stable center of gravity.</li><li><strong>Increased facial symmetry</strong> — relieving ascending and descending tension patterns.</li><li><strong>Better glute engagement</strong> — improved big toe activation leads to better posterior chain recruitment and increased lifting strength.</li><li>And more.</li></ul><p>All in all, this unique pairing is the missing approach most people need. From tooth to toe.</p>",
            "bottom_image": "shopify://shop_images/ac53c49b3b23d2cf6bae02ad4190b238928aee7e.jpg"
          }
        }
      },
